description: PIMS 4056 Regional IW FSP “Protection and Sustainable Use of the Dinaric Karst Transboundary Aquifer System (DIKTAS)

subproject.description: Countries recognize the Karst Aquifer System as a shared and highly vulnerable resource, and agree to take steps to deal with its transboundary implications. Regional agreement on priority TB issues, immediate and root causes; The strengthened collective knowledge and coordination among development plans of countries, projects, agencies and donors; Political commitment reached among countries on implementing priority legal, institutional and policy reforms for the protection and equitable utilization of the Karst Aquifer System; Long term sustainability of achievements enhanced through public and political awareness campaigns, stakeholder involvement and replication mechanisms.
subproject.gender code: No noticeable contribution to gender equality
